  "prompt": "I see roads on the Pok\u00e9mon GO map that glow faintly and are lighter, almost white. What is that?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, the roads that glow faintly and appear lighter or almost white on the map are **\"Routes.\"** Routes are a gameplay feature introduced in 2023 that allow players to follow predefined paths in the real world to earn rewards and encounter special Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n### Key Features of Routes:\n1. **Pathfinding**: Routes are designed by Niantic or submitted by players via the Wayfarer system. They represent a specific path you can follow in the game.\n2. **Rewards**: Walking a Route can give you rewards like Zygarde Cells (used to change Zygarde's Forme), XP, Stardust, and items.\n3. **Special Encounters**: Some Pok\u00e9mon may spawn more frequently along Routes, including rare or region-specific Pok\u00e9mon.\n4. **Exploration**: Routes encourage exploration of new areas and can lead you to discover interesting real-world locations.\n\n### How to Use Routes:\n1. **Access**: Open the Nearby Pok\u00e9mon menu (bottom right of the map) and tap the \"Routes\" tab to see available Routes nearby.\n2. **Start a Route**: Select a Route and tap \"Follow\" to begin.\n3. **Complete the Route**: Walk the path as indicated on the map to complete the Route and earn rewards.\n\nIf you see these glowing roads, it\u2019s a great opportunity to explore and take advantage of the bonuses they offer!",
